phrases: Hey, where are we supposed to take these journals?
Right as I was about to talk to Onodera!
Did not the teacher just tell us to take it to the prep room?
It is the science prep room, got it?
Do not go to the music room by mistake again!
Actually, the other day we figured we should start calling each other by our first names.
One of her friends mentioned to her how odd it was that we were not on a first-name basis,
despite how long we have been dating.
Still not used to it, though.
Damn it, I hate having to flaunt my relationship in front of Onodera!
She beat you to it, huh?
Why do not you just start calling him by his first name, too?
Oh, she was on her way to the science prep room.
The truth is, there is something I wanted to talk about, but without letting her know.
Since everybody seems to be present, could you all spare a moment, please?
You see, today is Mistress's birthday.
Thus, so that she may enjoy her special day,
I am currently planning a surprise party for her.
I would very much like to invite you to the party.
If you were to attend, I am sure that Mistress would be overjoyed.
That means we will have to get her presents and stuff.
Well, I suppose if you absolutely insist,
being that you are Mistress's boyfriend and all...
I might be inclined to invite you.
Well, not that I would even want to see your ugly mug.
If I am that revolting to you, then I will not bother!
It would be awkward, anyway, being the only guy.
After school, you two go buy her a present together!
Miyamoto, why are not you coming?!
Actually, I have had a stomachache all day.
You had two Lunch Special A's today!
Look, you will be able to pick out a gift faster if you bounce ideas off each other!
Okay, you two meet up by the cafe at five!
And show up in your normal clothes!
Even though you are not coming?
Man, I cannot believe how bossy Miyamoto always manages to be.
I can never figure out what is going through her mind.
I mean, meeting up with a girl here of all places?
That makes it look like we are on a date!
If this is a date, thenputting aside that fake date
that would mean that my first date ever would be with Onodera!
Picking out a present together, you cannot call that a real date, can you?!
Damn it, I have no clue!
Come to think of it, I never said that I would wait inside.
A-All right, then, should we get on with figuring out what we are getting for Chitoge-chan?
So she wants me to act like nothing happened?
Does not matter how many times I see her, I will never get over how cute she looks in her normal clothes.
I bet she saw me too!
I wonder what we look like to others?
Do they think she is my girlfriend?!
Or are you planning to look for that boy you made that promise with ten years ago?
As if I could just casually ask her about that!
What do you think she would really like for her birthday?
Come to think of it, I do not know when Onodera's birthday is.
If it has not passed yet, maybe then I could give her something.
Let us go to all the shops and figure out what we will get her!
I am sure that will be faster.
I will have plenty of time to ask her.
Thank goodness we found something nice!
I wonder if Chitoge-chan will like it.
It was all over in the blink of an eye.
There were so many things I wanted to talk to her about!
But the whole time my heart felt like it was going to burst!
Did you have fun today, Ichijou-kun?
Ruri-chan forced you to tag along with me today,
so I was wondering if you were just humoring me.
I had a good time, okay?
Hey, do you mind if we take a little detour?
Who knew there was a place like this at the end of that narrow alley?
No way would anyone find it!
I found it by accident, years ago.
Oh, crap, that makes me so happy!
But should she really be telling me about it, then?
By the way, who else knows about it?
I am guessing that Miyamoto, and...
You cannot tell anyone about it, okay?
You sure you want to share such an important secret with me?
I had a good time today too,
so this is kind of my way of thanking you.
What am I going to do?
Come to think of it, has not Onodera been a little aggressive today?
Our little secret has a great ring to it!
I should respond to Onodera's feelings, so...
I will not tell a soul!
Oh, wow, calling you by your first name is so embarrassing.
It is so much easier to just call you Ichijou-kun.
For a moment there, I thought she was...
No, that was just me reacting to the word promise.
There is no way things could be that convenient.
Did I really make you that uncomfortable by using your first name?
There is something I have wanted to know.
Take advantage of the great mood right now,
and just ask her when her birthday is.
And then ask her if it is okay to take her out to celebrate.
But it might be too awkward if it were just the two of us.
Anyway, if I could celebrate Onodera's birthday with her...
About the girl I made that promise with ten years ago...
I was feeling so self-conscious that I just blurted it out!
How am I going to play this down now?
If I spring a question like that on her out of nowhere,
there is no way she would understand!
You mentioned it before, did not you, Ichijou-kun?
That there is someone you made a promise with ten years ago.
I have someone like that too.
Although my memory is fuzzy since it is from my childhood.
Ten years ago, the summer when I was five...
I became friends with a certain boy,
and I received this key when we parted ways.
I cannot remember his face or his name anymore,
but the one thing I do remember is...
he was wearing the same kind of locket that you wear.
When you asked me before if I would ever seen your locket,
I was so taken aback that I automatically denied it.
It was only that one summer that I played with him.
But back then I was very shy,
Somehow, I felt I could trust him.
Now that I think of it, he might have been my...
That is why I was so surprised when I first saw your locket.
I thought that, just maybe, you were the same person, Ichijou-kun.
So that is why Onodera said that back then.
Even if it was ten years ago, and you were just kids...
Maybe it is still important to her.
I do not think that is quite right.
What are you doing, Ichijou Raku!
Sorry, Onodera, let us pick this up again later.
If... If Onodera is the girl I made that promise with...
There is still no proof, however.
If there was a simple way to just confirm it...
What do Chitoge-chan's parents do for a living?
What am I going to do?
My present is not all that great.
Mistress would never measure people by the price of their gifts.
What is up with that smug face?
Seishirou-chan, do not be such a stranger!
Wh-What are you all doing here?
As it is your birthday, I have taken the liberty of secretly inviting all your friends!
I have not told anybody that my family is a bunch of gangsters!
You still freak out over that?
What do you mean, over that?
Because of that, I never had any real friends, remember?
Of course I am freaking out!
Would not you know, this girl's family is...
Of like the yakuza in Japan.
Chitoge-chan, you are a total rich girl!
Because that makes you the same as Ichijou-kun, right?
All right, this is where we will be holding the party.
A very happy birthday to you!
Hey, so you turned sixteen today, eh, Mistress?
This kind of surprise never gets old, does it?
Are those your friends with you?
This the first time you have ever brought friends home, is not it?
Hey, young ladies, nice to meet you!
Oh, uh, yes, it is so nice to meet you!
You do not seem like your usual self today, Mistress.
Well, well, I see that your friends have come to the party as well.
Is that Master Raku from the Ichijou clan?
That certainly puts me on the spot.
After all, I am sure that you have the most splendid gift for Mistress.
I am starting to have reservations about presenting her my own gift.
I swear he is becoming more obvious with each passing second.
It is not that great, but...
Please take a look at our gift to you!
One thousand Japanese folk CDs and a year's supply of bananas!
Chitoge-chan, you like Japanese folk songs?
I am sure that it will pale in comparison to yours, Young Master.
Well, I do not have a license, so no thanks.
Come on, come on, you, too!
Damn it, could you make it any harder to hand someone a present?
Hey, little punk, is this what I think it is?
You would not be saying that Mistress is a gorilla, would you?
I was trying to be serious!
When I saw it in the store, I thought it was perfect!
You okay with something like that, Mistress?
Well, if Mistress is okay with it, we are okay with it.
You can smile like that too?
Yeah, I am taking a break.
Still, I have to say, your taste in presents really sucks.
So you put on an act after all.
If you do not like it, you can just toss it, okay?
If I do not cherish it, then people will start to suspect us.
So I am going to cherish it.
Because I have no choice, okay?
Do not tell me you actually really like it deep down!
You are going to cherish it, huh?
Damn it, you had me fooled with how sweetly you said it.
My heart even skipped a beat just now.
Wait, why is my heart skipping a beat for her?
I just found out Onodera could possibly be my promise girl!
It is not a stretch to say that I have met the girl I am destined to be with!
There is something that I have been wanting to ask you for the longest time.
Why are you being so formal now?
The girl that you said you met ten years ago...
Are you still in love with her?
You are still going on about that?
I told you, that is not what she and I were like
The girl from ten years ago...
I have not necessarily confirmed anything,
but what I found out means that it has to be Onodera, right?
